REV LEVEL:  0                                DATE CHANGED:  DECEMBER 20, 1985 

TYPE:  SOFTWARE
HARDWARE:  ENGINE
SUBJECT:  INITIALIZATION OF TYMSAT SLOT UNDER ISIS


MACHINES AFFECTED: ALL 7/32 AND ENGINES RUNNING TYMSAT SLOT UNDER ISIS.

SYMPTOM:       THE PROBLEM HAS OCCURRED IN ISIS CONFIGURATIONS IN
               AUSTRALIA, JAPAN, SWEDEN, AND MOST RECENTLY IN SWITZERLAND
               AS WELL AS IN AN ISIS LAB ENVIRONMENT. THE INDICATIONS ARE
               AFTER LOADING OR RESTARTING THE ISIS CODE, TRANSMIT DATA
               LEADS FOR THE LOW-SPEED PORTS (ASYNCHRONOUS) ARE IN THE
               WRONG STATE. I.E. IN A SPACING STATE INSTEAD OF A
               MARKING STATE.(GREEN LED'S ARE LIT FOR TRANSMIT DATA ON
               MONITOR PANEL). THIS CONDITION DOES NOT NECESSARILLY APPLY
               TO ALL PORTS, BUT IF ANY PORTS INITIALIZE TO THIS
               CONDITION - YOU GOT THE BUG. ONLY DATA TERMINAL READY (DTR)
               SHOULD BE ACTIVE AFTER THE TYMSAT SLOT IS RUNNING AND NO
               LOG-INS ARE YET PRESENT.


               IT APPEARS TO BE A SOFTWARE BUG WHICH IS CONFIGURATION
               DEPENDENT, SO DON@T EXPECT THE SYMPTOM TO MANIFEST ITSELF
               IN ALL MACHINES RUNNING TYMSAT SLOT UNDER ISIS.

ACTION:        UNTIL THE BUG IS FIXED, THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURES SHOULD HELP
               IN RELIEVING THE SYMPTOM:-

       (1)     DEPRESS 'INIT' BUTTON ON CONSOLE WHILE THE CODE IS RUNNING.
               THIS CAUSES SYSTEM CLEAR TO BE GENERATED AND THE CODE TO
               RE-INITIALIZE.
         NOTE: IT IS MANDATORY THAT ECO'S 79-53 AND 79-54 BE INSTALLED
               IF YOU PERFORM ACTION ITEM #1. ATTEMPTING THIS, WHILE
               NOT HAVING THESE ECO'S INSTALLED, WILL RESULT IN CAUSING
               A MEMORY PARITY ERROR AT THE LOCATION OF EXECUTION AT THE
               TIME THE "INIT" BUTTON WAS DEPRESSED. IF YOU DO NOT HAVE
               THESE ECO'S IN A MACHINE WHICH IS EXHIBITTING THIS
               PROBLEM YOU ARE ADVISED TO ATTEMPT ACTION ITEM #2 AS AN
               ALTERNATIVE PROCEDURE.

       (2)     HALT THE CODE, AND RESTART FROM ADDRESS '70'.

       (3)     HALT THE TYMSAT SLOT AND RESTART THE SLOT.

NOTE:          DO NOT USE ALL THREE METHODS - IT APPEARS THAT DIFFERENT
               SOLUTIONS ARE APPLICABLE TO THE PARTICULAR CONFIGURATION.
               (HOPE YOURS IS AMONGST THOSE ABOVE)

               ALSO, AFTER YOU GET TRANSMIT DATA IN THE CORRECT STATE IT
               APPEARS TO REMAIN CORRECT UNTIL THE MACHINE IS EITHER
               RESTARTED OR RELOADED.

               TO ASSIST IN GATHERING INFO FOR DEBUGGING - IF YOU SEE THIS
               SYMPTOM PLEASE SEND ME INFO RE. NODE # AND CODE.

RESOLUTION:    THE ISIS DEVELOPMENT GROUP HAVE BEEN INFORMED OF THIS
               PROBLEM AND HAVE MANAGED TO RECREATE IT IN A LAB ENVIRONMENT
               IT HAS BEEN IDENTIFIED AS A BUG DURING INITIALISATION OF
               THE CODE DUE TO HAVING INTERRUPTS DISABLED FOR SUFFICIENT
               TIME TO INTERFERE WITH THE ASYNC RING HANDLING.
               IF TESTING OF THE NEW CODE IS SUCCESSFUL A NEW VERSION WILL
               BE RELEASED IN APPROXIMATELY TWO WEEKS TIME.

TKS.


