TYPE:  SOFTWARE
HARDWARE:  ALL
SUBJECT:  PROBLEM WITH LOADII


PROBLEM:       THERE IS A BUG IN THE VERSION OF LOADII ON SYSTEM 25
               INVOLVING THE LOADING OF VERY SMALL FILES (60 RECORDS OR LESS)
               THIS MEANS MOST DIAGNOSTICS AND THE VARIAN 32K BOOTSTRAP
               CANNOT BE LOADED USING THIS VERSION. TO CORRECT THIS PROBLEM
               THERE ARE NOW TWO VERSIONS OF LOADII ON SYSTEM 25. WE ARE
               LEAVING THE VERSION WITH BUG TO DETERMINE IF OTHER BUGS EXIST
               BEFORE RELEASING AN ENTIRELY NEW VERSION, SO PLEASE USE IT
               WHENEVER POSSIBLE AND REPORT ABNORMALITIES TO RON VIVIER.
               SHORT FILES CAN BE LOADED USING LOAD2.


               (NETCON:25)LOADII       (VERSION 1.01  HAS BUG)
               (NETCON:25)LOAD2        (VERSION 11  WORKS O.K.)

               (NETCON:33)LOADII       (VERSION 11    WORKS O.K.)


