CFB NO.:   22                                        DATE:  FEBRUARY 26, 1980 

REV LEVEL:  0                                DATE CHANGED:  DECEMBER 20, 1985 

TYPE:  INFORMATION
HARDWARE:  ENGINE
SUBJECT:  ENHANCED SYNCHRONOUS SOFTWARE/HARDWARE IMPLEMENTATION


        VERSION 430 - TYMNET I - ENGINE REMOTE CODE SPECIFICATIONS

                       SYNCHRONOUS MICROCODE SUPPORT



    A.  .TYM FILE ADDITIONS/CHANGES

        THE FOLLOWING EQUATES ARE AFFECTED BY VERSON 430 CODE:

        FOR ENHANCED SYNCHRONOUS SUPPORT, SET MICRO EQUAL TO '2'.

        MICRO    EQ   0   NO ASYNC OR SYNC SUPPORT (DEFAULT)
        MICRO    EQ   1   ENHANCED ASYNCHRONOUS SUPPORT ONLY.
        MICRO    EQ   2   ENHANCED ASYNC & SYNC SUPPORT.

        VERSION 430 CRASH STOP OPTION.

        CRSTOP   EQ   1   HALT SYSTEM ON CRASH OCCURRANCE.
        CRSTOP   EQ   0   ALLOW AUTOMATIC RESTART ON CRASH OCCURRANCE.

        IF THE .TYM FILE SPECIFIES "CRSTOP EQ 1", THE ENGINE REMOTE
        CODE WILL HALT AFTER A CRASH INSTEAD OF RESTARTING AUTOMATICALLY.
        THIS IS USEFUL FOR CERTAIN DEBUGGING SITUATIONS AND SHOULD ONLY
        BE USED AS SUCH.  WHEN A CRASH OCCURS, REGISTER SETS 0 AND F
        ARE SAVED AND THE MACHINE IS HALTED.

        IF "CRSTOP" IS NOT DEFINED, THE ASSEMBLER WILL DEFAULT AND SET
        "CRSTOP  EQ  0" AND ALLOW AUTOMATIC RESTART AFTER EACH CRASH.

        MEMORY SHUFFLER SUPPORT.

        MEMORY SHUFFLER SUPPORT HAS BEEN REMOVED FROM VERSION 430
        REMOTE CODE.  IF "MLINKS" IS DEFINED TO BE GREATER THAN '0',
        "MLINKS" WILL BE FORCED TO '0' DURING ASSEMBLY AND THE MESSAGE:
        *** MEMORY SHUFFLER NOT SUPPORTED - CANCELLED! *** IS OUTPUT
        TO THE TERMINAL DURING ASSEMBLY.  "MLINKS" NEED NOT BE SPECIFIED.

        MLINKS   EQ  0   NO MEMORY SHUFFLER SPECIFED
        MLINKS   EQ  N   MEMORY SUFFLER SPECIFIED - FORCE DEFAULT TO '0'




















    B.  VERSION 430 HARDWARE CHANGE REQUIREMENTS

        TO UTILIZE THE ENHANCED SYNCHRONOUS FEATURES, AN ENGINE MUST
        HAVE THE FOLLOWING HARDWARE CHANGES INSTALLED:

        1.)  ENHANCED SYNCHRONOUS MICROCODE.

             A.  MAPPING PROMS:    MPS15-0  ROM & I/O POSITION H-2
                                   MPS15-1  ROM & I/O POSITION J-2

             B.  MICROCODE PROMS:  S15-00 THRU S15-07  ROM & I/O POS A3-A10
                                   S15-10 THRU S15-17  ROM & I/O POS B3-B10
                                   S15-20 THRU S15-27  ROM & I/O POS C3-C10
                                   S15-30 THRU S15-37  ROM & I/O POS D3-D10
             INSTRUCTIONS ADDED TO THE ENHANCED SYNCHRONOUS MICROCODE
             CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING:

                A.)  SCAN - SCANS THROUGH SYNC INPUT RING FOR DATA.
                B.)  ALIGN - ALIGNS DATA FROM INPUT RING INTO BUFFER.
                C.)  RTDCOPY - PERFORMS RECORD TEARDOWN AND COPY FUNCTION.
                D.)  RMAKECOPY - PERFORMS RECORD MAKER FUNCTION.
                E.)  CHECKSUM - PERFORMS VERTICL AND DIAGONAL CHECKSUM.
                F.)  GCI - GETS A CHARACTER FROM A SPECIFIED BUFFER.
                G.)  WCI - WRITES A CHARACTER TO A SPECIFIED BUFFER.

             SYNC CARD INTERRUPTS MAY BE SERVICED IN MICROCODE BY SETTING
             BIT SIX (6) OF THE PSW 'ON' (HEX 0200).  IF BIT 6 IS RESET,
             CONVENTIONAL INTERRUPTS ARE TAKEN.

        2.)  THE CPU BACKPLANE MUST BE MODIFIED TO ACCOMODATE INTERRUPT
             LEVEL "1" IN PLACE OF INTERRUPT LEVEL "2" FOR THE
             SYNCHRONOUS CARD.

             REMOVE  RACK10/TACK10 BYPASS JUMPER AND INSTALL
             RACK20/TACK20 BYPASS JUMPER FOR CARD SLOT(S) WITH
             SYNCHRONOUS BOARDS INSTALLED.

             DELETE CONNECTOR 0 BACKPLANE WIREWRAP AS FOLLOWS:

             SIGNAL   FROM    TO

             RACK10   127-0   227-0 (TACK10)

             ADD CONNECTOR 0 BACKPLANE WIREWRAP AS FOLLOWS:

             SIGNAL   FROM    TO

             RACK20   122-0   222-0 (TACK20)












        3.)  SYNCHRONOUS INTERFACE BOARD(S) MUST BE MODIFIED TO ACCOMODATE
             INTERRUPT LEVEL "1" IN PLACE OF INTERRUPT LEVEL "2".  REFERENCE
             ECO NO. 80-24.

             CUT TRACES NEAR BACKPLANE CONNECTOR AS FOLLOWS:

             SIGNAL     FROM    TO

             ATN20      E1-8    223-0                                       ]
             RACK20     D2-5    122-0                                       ]
             TACK20     E1-6    222-0                                       ]

             ADD JUMPER WIRE TO BOARD AS FOLLOWS:

             SIGNAL     FROM    TO

             ATN10      E1-8    226-0                                       ]
             RACK10     D2-5    127-0                                       ]
             TACK10     E1-6    227-0                                       ]

        4.)  THIS CHANGE APPLIES TO MACHINES WITH THE FOLLOWING
             REVISON LEVELS ONLY.

             CPU AND/OR BACKPLANE AFFECTED:   ALL

             SYNCHRONOUS I/O BOARD PART NUMBER:  ASB212-1  REVISION: ALL

    C.  SOFTWARE COMPATABILITY.

        THE ENGINE ENHANCED SYNC MODIFIED AS ABOVE IS DOWNWARD COMPATABLE
        WITH PREVIOUS RELEASES OF REMOTE CODE.

        VERSION 430 ENGINE REMOTE CODE MAY BE RUN ON ALL THREE LEVELS OF
        ENGINES BY USING THE APPROPRIATE DEFINITION OF "MICRO" IN THE
        .TYM FILE.  I.E. NON-ENHANCED, ENHANCED ASYNC, ENHANCED ASYNC
        WITH ENHANCED SYNC.

    D.  SOFTWARE FEATURES ADDED TO VERSION 430

        1.)  THE VERSION NUMBER CONTAINED IN THE REMOTE CODE REFLECTS
             THE PRESENCE OF ENHANCED SYNC MICROCODE SUPPORT AND/OR
             ENHANCED ASYNC MICROCODE SUPPORT AS FOLLOWS:

             IF MICRO  EQ  0,  VERSION NUMBER WILL EQUAL 000430 (OCTAL)
             IF MICRO  EQ  1,  VERSION NUMBER WILL EQUAL 100430 (OCTAL)
             IF MICRO  EQ  2,  VERSION NUMBER WILL EQUAL 140430 (OCTAL)














        2.)  THE FOLLOWING PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT COUNTERS ARE ADDED
             FEATURES OF THE REMOTE CODE:

             A.  NUMBER OF BUFFER ZAPS
             B.  NUMBER OF PRINTER CHARACTERS OUTPUT
             C.  NUMBER OF DOWNLINE LOAD INPUT CHARACTERS
             D.  NUMBER OF DOWNLINE LOAD OUTPUT CHARACTERS
             E.  NUMBER OF PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT OUTPUT CHARACTERS
             F.  NUMBER OF ASYNC NOISE CHARACTERS INPUT

        3.)  EXPANDED BUFFER STORAGE
             THE AMOUNT OF BUFFER STORAGE IN THE NODE IS NO LONGER
             RESTRICTED TO A MAXIMUM OF 64K BYTES.  VERSION
             430 ALLOWS ALL UNUSED MEMORY AVAILABLE IN THE CONFIGURATION
             TO BE ALLOCATED AS BUFFER SPACE.

             THE MESSAGE: "BUFFER SPACE ALLOCATED = <N> BYTES DECIMAL"
             IS OUTPUT AT ASSEMBLY TIME TO INDICATE THE SIZE OF BUFFER
             STORAGE.

    E.  DELETIONS FROM VERSION 430 REMOTE CODE

        1.)  CIRCUIT TRACING FEATURES ADDED IN VERSION 426 ARE NO LONGER
             REQUIRED AND HAVE BEEN DELETED FROM VERSION 430.

    F.  SOFTWARE CORRECTIONS IN VERSION 430 REMOTE CODE

        1.)  A SOFTWARE ERROR HAS BEEN CORRECTED WHEREBY THE FORMAT OF
             A MESSAGE TO THE SUPERVISOR INDICATED THE WRONG SIZE FOR A
             BUFFER ZAPPED.  THE PREVIOUS VERSIONS INDICTED A BUFFER
             SIZE 8 TIMES LARGER THAN ACTUALLY OCCURRED.  THIS RESULTED
             IN NO VISIBLE AFFECT EXTERNAL TO THE SYSTEM.

        2.)  THE DOWNLINE LOAD LOGIC WITH PREVIOUS VERSIONS WOULD WAIT
             INDEFINITELY IF A BREAK IN COMMUNICATIONS WITH THE HOST
             SYSTEM OCCURRED DURING INITIATION OF THE DOWNLINE LOAD.
             A TIMER HAS BEEN ADDED TO VERSION 430 WHICH WILL TIME OUT
             IF TWO MINUTES HAS ELAPSED WITHOUT RECEIPT OF THE TARGET
             LINE NUMBER FROM THE HOST. THE CIRCUIT TO THE HOST
             IS ZAPPED UPON TIMEOUT.



















        EXAMPLE NAD ASSEMBLER TERMINAL OUTPUT WHEN ASSEMBLING VERSION 430
        REMOTE CODE:


        *** MEMORY SHUFFLER NOT SUPPORTED - CANCELLED! ***

                        *** VERSION 140430 REMOTE ***

        MEMORY SIZE 128 K

        ENHANCED ASYNC MICROCODE

        ENHANCED SYNC MICROCODE

        PERFORMANCE MONITORING ENABLED

        BUFFER SPACE ALLOCATED = 46670 BYTES DECIMAL

        END OF ASSEMBLY

        LISTER WORKING
