CFB NO.:   23                                        DATE:  FEBRUARY 26, 1980 

REV LEVEL:  0                                DATE CHANGED:  DECEMBER 20, 1985 

TYPE:  HARDWARE
HARDWARE:  ENGINE
SUBJECT:  INTERNAL DVM IN PIONEER MAGNETICS POWER SUPPLIES


MACHINES AFFECTED:             TYMNET ENGINE


PROBLEM:       IT HAS BEEN FOUND THAT A NUMBER OF MACHINES WERE SHIPPED TO
               THE FIELD WITH THE INTERNAL DVM OUT OF CALIBRATION. THIS
               CAN CAUSE BOTH PROBLEMS IN THE OPERATION OF THE MACHINE AS
               WELL AS MARGINAL POWER FAIL DETECT OPERATION.

ACTION:        ON ALL ENGINES, CHECK WITH YOUR PORTABLE DVM THE +5, +16.5,
               AND -16.5 VOLTAGES ON THE BACKPLANE.
               (THE +5V SHOULD MEASURE +5.15 TO +5.20 ON THE BACKPLANE)
               IF THERE IS MORE THAN 100MILLIVOLTS DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE
               VOLTAGE MEASURED AND THE VOLTAGE INDICATED ON THE INTERNAL
               DVM IN THE POWER SUPPLY, LABEL THE POWER SUPPLY METER AS
               UNCALIBRATED AND READJUST THE VOLTAGES TO THEIR CORRECT LEVELS
               WHILE THE MACHINE IS RUNNING.


