CFB NO.:   25                                        DATE:  APRIL 10, 1980    

REV LEVEL:  0                                DATE CHANGED:  DECEMBER 20, 1985 

TYPE:  HARDWARE
HARDWARE:  ENGINE
SUBJECT:  MULTI-FUNCTION CARD WATCHDOG TIMER/BOOT SWITCH SETTINGS.


       THERE ARE TWO (2) REVISIONS OF THE MULTIFUNCTION CARD (ASB252-1)
       CURRENTLY IN THE FIELD WITH DIFFERENT TYPES OF BOOT SWITCH.

       THE ASB252-1 REV C BOARD HAS A TWO POSITION BOOT SWITCH.
       WHEN THE SWITCH IS IN THE "DOWN" POSITION - THE WATCHDOG TIMER
       IS DISABLED.
       WHEN THE SWITCH IS IN THE "UP" POSITION - THE SYNC LOADER IS
       FORCED INTO CORE AND IF THE SWITCH IS LEFT "UP", THE WATCHDOG TIMER
       IS ENABLED. IF THE SWITCH IS PUT BACK TO THE "DOWN" POSITION,
       SUBSEQUENT TO FORCING THE SYNC LOADER INTO CORE, THE WATCHDOG TIMER
       WILL BE DISABLED.
       NOTE: A POTENTIAL PROBLEM EXISTS WITH THIS REV OF BOARD. THE CIRCUIT
       IS DESIGNED IN SUCH A WAY THAT IT IS POSSIBLE TO CAUSE THE "BOOT
       FUNCTION" TO BE GENERATED IF THE SWITCH IS MOVED TO THE "DOWN"
       POSITION, TO DISABLE THE WATCHDOG TIMER, WHILE RUNNING CODE

       THE ASB252-1 REV D BOARD HAS A THREE (3) POSITION BOOT SWITCH.
       WHEN THE SWITCH IS IN THE "DOWN" POSITION, THE WATCHDOG TIMER IS
       ENABLED.
       WHEN THE SWITCH IS IN THE "CENTER" POSITION, THE WATCHDOG TIMER
       IS DISABLED.
       THE "UP" POSITION IS A MOMENTARY ACTION SWITCH CAUSING THE "SYNC
       LOADER" TO BE FORCED INTO CORE AND THE SWITCH WILL THEN RETURN TO
       THE CENTER POSITION.

ACTION PROBLEMS HAVE OCCURED  DUE TO THE INABILITY FOR NETWORK CONTROL
       TO PERFORM "DLOADS" ON MACHINES HAVING THE WATCHDOG TIMER DISABLED.

       THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURE SHOULD BE IMPLEMENTED IMMEDIATELY:

       1.  ON ALL MACHINES HAVING SYNC LOADER PROMS AND SUITABLE SOFTWARE
           TO RESET THE WATCHDOG TIMER THE SWITCH SHOULD BE SET SUCH THAT
           THE WATCHDOG TIMER IS ENABLED.

           (ASB252-1) REV C:     SWITCH IN "UP" POSITION
           (ASB252-1) REV D:     SWITCH IN "DOWN" POSITION

       2.  THE WATCHDOG TIMER SHOULD ONLY BE DISABLED ON MACHINES SUFFERING
           REPETITIVE CRASHES WHEREBY CRASH ANALYSIS IS BEING HINDERED BY
           THE AUTOMATIC RETURN TO THE "SYNC LOADER". IN SUCH SITUATIONS,
           NETWORK CONTROL SHOULD ALWAYS BE INFORMED OF ANY MACHINE HAVING
           THE WATCHDOG TIMER DISABLED. THIS WILL PREVENT A "DLOAD" COMMAND
           BEING ISSUED TO THESE MACHINES AND SUBSEQUENT MAINTENANCE
           INTERVENTION.


CFB NO.:   26                                        DATE:  APRIL 28, 1980    

REV LEVEL:  0                                DATE CHANGED:  DECEMBER 20, 1985 

TYPE:  HARDWARE
HARDWARE:  DATAPRINTER
SUBJECT:  DATAPRINTER DPC/CDC I/O ADAPTER BOARD VERSIONS


WARNING:       THERE ARE TWO VERSIONS OF THE DATAPRINTER DPC/CDC I/O
               ADAPTER BOARD (#12056) AND ONLY ONE VERSION IS
               SUITABLE FOR TYMSHARE APPLICATIONS. THE TWO VERSIONS
               ARE IDENTIFIED AS PART NUMBERS 12056G1 AND 12056G2.
               THE DIFFERENCES ARE AS FOLLOWS:

               #12056G1 - SHORT LINE DRIVER/RECEIVER CAPABLE OF DRIVING
                          PRINTER UP TO A MAXIMUM OF 10FT.

               #12056G2 - LONG LINE DRIVER/RECEIVER CAPABLE OF DRIVING
                          PRINTER UP TO 500FT.

               TYPICAL TYMSHARE INSTALLATIONS ARE INVARIABLY DRIVING THE
               PRINTER IN EXCESS OF 10FT. THIS REQUIRES THAT THE I/O
               ADAPTER BOARD ALWAYS BE PART NUMBER 12056G2, TO INSURE
               ERROR FREE DATA TRANSFER.

ACTION:        PURGE ALL SPARES OF ADAPTER BOARD #12056G1 AND ATTEMPT
               TO EXCHANGE FOR #12056G2 THROUGH DATAPRINTER.


